==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: elephant-tusk
<hw>elephant-tusk</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>an annual of the southern U.S.
and Mexico (<spn>Proboscidea louisianica</spn>) having large whitish or
yellowish flowers mottled with purple and a long curving beak.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> common unicorn plant, devil's claw, common devil's
claw, proboscis flower, ram's horn, <spn>Proboscidea
louisianica</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elephantine</ent>⟦br⟧
